Barry, Barry, Nick and Hyde is back.

00:02:59.900 --> 00:03:01.100
He stood on a crate.

00:03:01.100 --> 00:03:02.100
She slouched.

00:03:02.100 --> 00:03:02.940
Why?

00:03:02.940 --> 00:03:04.620
It's part of our television heritage.

00:03:04.620 --> 00:03:06.740
Something strange was going on with Don Adams

00:03:06.740 --> 00:03:08.820
and Barbara Felden during the Get Smart years.

00:03:08.820 --> 00:03:11.420
They tried to be subtle, but they kept changing heights.

00:03:11.420 --> 00:03:12.900
Sometimes she's taller.

00:03:12.900 --> 00:03:14.460
Sometimes he's taller.

00:03:14.460 --> 00:03:15.460
Here it's Felden.

00:03:15.460 --> 00:03:17.660
But in the close-up, it's Adams again.

00:03:17.660 --> 00:03:19.980
The wide shot, however, doesn't lie.

00:03:19.980 --> 00:03:23.460
Sizing Adams up at 5.7, Felden at 5.9.

00:03:23.460 --> 00:03:26.700
Two subtle inches double four in our television heritage.

00:03:26.700 --> 00:03:30.660
And Get Smart, weeknights on Nickelodeon.

00:03:30.660 --> 00:03:33.900
Welcome to SNCC, Saturday Night Nickelodeon.

00:03:33.900 --> 00:03:36.300
Now you'll know what everyone's talking about

00:03:36.300 --> 00:03:42.460
on Monday morning.

00:03:42.460 --> 00:03:44.220
Never outgrow his cartoons.

00:03:44.220 --> 00:03:46.780
You could be 5, 15, or 50.

00:03:46.780 --> 00:03:52.050
When the anvil falls on that guy's head, it's a scream.

00:03:52.050 --> 00:03:53.930
But cartoons are kind of special.

00:03:53.930 --> 00:03:55.410
Not everything lasts.

00:03:55.410 --> 00:03:57.930
Like it or not, some stuff you just outgrow.

00:03:57.930 --> 00:04:00.130
Here are some examples.

00:04:00.130 --> 00:04:01.450
Gum wrapper chain.

00:04:01.450 --> 00:04:03.010
When I was a kid, my jaw used to ache

00:04:03.010 --> 00:04:05.050
from all the gum I chewed.

00:04:05.050 --> 00:04:06.850
I could work on that chain for hours.

00:04:06.850 --> 00:04:09.130
I was determined to make it a mile long,

00:04:09.130 --> 00:04:13.090
but now I've kind of cut it out.

00:04:13.090 --> 00:04:14.770
And then there's pigtails.

00:04:14.770 --> 00:04:16.370
They used to be my hairstyle of choice,

00:04:16.370 --> 00:04:17.970
but now that I'm a little older,

00:04:17.970 --> 00:04:19.970
I've decided to let my hair down.

00:04:19.970 --> 00:04:21.330
And what about batons?

00:04:21.330 --> 00:04:22.450
I used to think that trolling them

00:04:22.450 --> 00:04:24.010
was a pretty flashy maneuver,

00:04:24.050 --> 00:04:27.330
but then I realized there's just a flash in the pan.

00:04:27.330 --> 00:04:28.810
Most of the good things in life come with their own

00:04:28.810 --> 00:04:30.450
built-in expiration date.

00:04:30.450 --> 00:04:31.970
You can try to keep using them after that,

00:04:31.970 --> 00:04:35.010
but odds are, it'll be a stale experience.

00:04:35.010 --> 00:04:37.890
Knowing when to move on is what growing up is all about.

00:04:37.890 --> 00:04:39.890
But pretty soon, I'll be trading in the trappings

00:04:39.890 --> 00:04:43.290
of childhood for the perks of full-blown adulthood.

00:04:43.290 --> 00:04:45.130
I'm more than ready to trade in my piggy bank

00:04:45.130 --> 00:04:46.410
for a credit card.

00:04:46.410 --> 00:04:48.650
I can definitely handle having my 10 o'clock curfew

00:04:48.650 --> 00:04:50.330
pushed back to midnight.

00:04:50.330 --> 00:04:52.170
But the thing I'm most ready to take on

00:04:52.170 --> 00:04:53.930
is a set of wheels.

00:04:53.930 --> 00:04:56.690
In a few months, when I finally get my driver's license,

00:04:56.690 --> 00:04:58.290
I'll be moving on so fast,

00:04:58.290 --> 00:05:01.530
some of the stuff I once liked will be left in the dust.

00:05:01.530 --> 00:05:58.330
Let's make this part of the graph a little more blue.

00:05:58.330 --> 00:05:59.330
What are you doing in my room?

00:05:59.330 --> 00:06:00.450
Making a bar graph.

00:06:00.450 --> 00:06:01.970
Making a mess is more like it.

00:06:01.970 --> 00:06:03.930
What is your junk doing all over everything?

00:06:03.930 --> 00:06:05.010
Clean the stuff up.

00:06:05.010 --> 00:06:06.610
I can't. This is for school.

00:06:06.610 --> 00:06:08.570
Besides, I knew Mom and Dad wouldn't mind.

00:06:08.570 --> 00:06:09.730
Well, I mind chimp-braining.

00:06:09.730 --> 00:06:12.170
It's my computer, so why would this chocolate slime

00:06:12.170 --> 00:06:13.170
and get out?

00:06:13.170 --> 00:06:14.730
But sis, am I reporting America's

00:06:14.730 --> 00:06:16.690
consumption of dairy products as due tomorrow

00:06:16.690 --> 00:06:18.930
when my computer doesn't do graphics?

00:06:18.930 --> 00:06:20.130
Well, then do it the old fashioned way.

00:06:20.130 --> 00:06:20.930
Use a ruler.

00:06:20.930 --> 00:06:22.410
Well, then it'll take hours.

00:06:22.410 --> 00:06:23.450
Better get cracking.

00:06:23.450 --> 00:06:24.130
Come on, sis.

00:06:24.130 --> 00:06:26.250
This is your brother you're talking to.

00:06:26.250 --> 00:06:26.810
That's right.

00:06:26.810 --> 00:06:28.690
The one guy who should know enough to stay out of my room

00:06:28.690 --> 00:06:29.770
without asking.

00:06:29.770 --> 00:06:32.010
What about the time I picked up your game pack and played?

00:06:32.010 --> 00:06:33.490
You totally freaked out.

00:06:33.490 --> 00:06:34.210
That was different.

00:06:34.210 --> 00:06:35.530
It was practically new.

00:06:35.530 --> 00:06:37.050
You left it lying around the living room.

00:06:37.050 --> 00:06:38.170
That makes a fair game.

00:06:38.170 --> 00:06:39.970
If it had been in your room, I would have asked.

00:06:39.970 --> 00:06:41.450
If I had asked you to use a computer,

00:06:41.450 --> 00:06:42.770
would you have let me?

00:06:42.770 --> 00:06:44.770
Maybe, but we'll never know now, will we?

00:06:44.770 --> 00:06:45.770
Beat it.

00:06:45.810 --> 00:06:46.810
Come on, sis.

00:06:46.810 --> 00:06:48.850
I'll give you one last chance to reconsider.

00:06:48.850 --> 00:06:50.490
OK.

00:06:50.490 --> 00:06:52.810
Don't let the door hit you on the way out.

00:06:52.810 --> 00:06:55.810
You've log off.

00:06:55.810 --> 00:06:57.610
Clarissa, what is your bike doing on the walk

00:06:57.610 --> 00:06:58.490
in front of the house?

00:06:58.490 --> 00:07:00.010
I just about broke my neck.

00:07:00.010 --> 00:07:01.970
I'll get it in a minute, mom.

00:07:01.970 --> 00:07:03.450
I don't understand.

00:07:03.450 --> 00:07:06.090
Is it so hard to put things away when you're done?

00:07:06.090 --> 00:07:08.770
Going out with Sam pretty soon anyway, it's almost bike.

00:07:08.770 --> 00:07:11.210
Clarissa, you bred this for that bike.

00:07:11.210 --> 00:07:12.930
I know, but that was three years ago.

00:07:12.930 --> 00:07:14.770
I'm practically driving now.

00:07:14.810 --> 00:07:17.610
I think that's a separate issue, dear.

00:07:17.610 --> 00:07:19.130
Has anybody seen my keys?

00:07:19.130 --> 00:07:21.330
Well, where were you when you last had them?

00:07:21.330 --> 00:07:22.770
Why do people always ask that?

00:07:22.770 --> 00:07:26.410
I mean, if I knew where they were, uh, forget it.

00:07:26.410 --> 00:07:27.850
Dad, I promise they're not in here.

00:07:27.850 --> 00:07:30.290
Boy, this quilt could use a wash.

00:07:30.290 --> 00:07:32.250
Hey, those things kind of neat.

00:07:32.250 --> 00:07:33.290
Where'd you get a sport?

00:07:33.290 --> 00:07:35.970
Can I at least borrow your ruler?

00:07:35.970 --> 00:07:37.890
What is everybody doing in my room?

00:07:37.890 --> 00:07:42.660
Hey, Sam.

00:07:42.660 --> 00:07:43.620
Hey, Clarissa.

00:07:43.620 --> 00:07:45.180
Ready to check out the new CD store?

00:07:45.180 --> 00:07:46.420
All ready.

00:07:46.420 --> 00:07:47.420
Hey, where's my bike?

00:07:47.780 --> 00:07:48.700
I guess Mom moved it.

00:07:48.700 --> 00:07:53.750
Come on, it must be in the backyard.

00:07:53.750 --> 00:07:54.630
Not here.

00:07:54.630 --> 00:08:04.180
It must have gone all the way and put it in the garage.

00:08:04.180 --> 00:08:05.340
Any luck?

00:08:05.340 --> 00:08:13.420
Garden weasel, manure bag, tether ball, no bike.

00:08:13.420 --> 00:08:14.620
Where do you think it could be?

00:08:14.620 --> 00:08:15.500
I don't know.

00:08:17.580 --> 00:08:19.460
Do you have a report to do on dairy products?

00:08:19.460 --> 00:08:20.140
Oh, I do.

00:08:20.140 --> 00:08:21.660
Ice cream is research.

00:08:21.660 --> 00:08:22.860
Have you seen my bike?

00:08:22.860 --> 00:08:25.180
I don't really keep tabs on your bike, sis.

00:08:25.180 --> 00:08:26.100
Not in the front yard.

00:08:26.100 --> 00:08:27.300
It's not in the backyard.

00:08:27.300 --> 00:08:30.300
It's not in the garage, so where is it?

00:08:30.300 --> 00:08:33.620
I think we can safely rule out spontaneous combustion

00:08:33.620 --> 00:08:36.340
or it being swallowed by a sinkhole.

00:08:36.340 --> 00:08:37.780
I hate to shock you with the obvious,

00:08:37.780 --> 00:08:41.140
but maybe it's been stolen.

00:08:41.140 --> 00:08:42.260
Stolen?

00:08:42.260 --> 00:08:43.380
Who would steal it?

00:08:43.380 --> 00:08:45.300
It's got to be somewhere.

00:08:45.300 --> 00:08:48.260
I'd love to help you look for it, sis, but I've got bar charts

00:08:48.260 --> 00:08:53.550
to do, remember?

00:08:53.550 --> 00:08:55.830
Boy, you hear about these things happening every day,

00:08:55.830 --> 00:08:58.990
but you never expect them to happen in your own front yard.

00:08:58.990 --> 00:09:01.150
Bikes disappear every day.

00:09:01.150 --> 00:09:03.270
Yeah, but this bike is different.

00:09:03.270 --> 00:09:04.110
This bike is mine.

00:09:04.550 --> 00:09:06.830
I know it was just an old three-speed with a bent pedal

00:09:06.830 --> 00:09:09.830
and a fake wicker basket, but I miss my dumb old bike.

00:09:09.830 --> 00:09:11.990
I can't believe I'm saying that, but it's true.

00:09:11.990 --> 00:09:14.310
I mean, it's my bike, and I hate to think about somebody

00:09:14.310 --> 00:09:15.950
else riding around on it.

00:09:15.950 --> 00:09:17.550
I mean, I relied on that bike.

00:09:17.550 --> 00:09:19.350
Now that I'm walking, my whole day

00:09:19.350 --> 00:09:22.310
got off on the wrong foot.

00:09:22.310 --> 00:09:25.670
I'd forgotten how long it takes to get around without wheels.

00:09:25.670 --> 00:09:27.790
By the time I got to school, Mrs. Strepermeyer

00:09:27.790 --> 00:09:30.230
locked the homeroom door.

00:09:30.230 --> 00:09:32.710
It's humiliating being known as the old bike.

00:09:32.750 --> 00:09:35.790
It's humiliating being known as the only kid in academic history

00:09:35.790 --> 00:09:40.350
trying to break into school.

00:09:40.350 --> 00:09:42.030
And after school, it took me forever

00:09:42.030 --> 00:09:46.830
to get to the pizza-pig out party with my friends.

00:09:46.830 --> 00:09:53.210
Anyway, you slice it, being without a bike really bites.

00:09:53.210 --> 00:09:55.130
As if that wasn't enough, I finally

00:09:55.130 --> 00:10:05.140
got to see murder on the Uptown Express.

00:10:05.140 --> 00:10:06.860
But since I missed the opening scene,

00:10:06.860 --> 00:10:10.060
I still don't know who'd done it.

00:10:10.060 --> 00:10:11.860
Boy, for a two-wheel vehicle designed

00:10:11.860 --> 00:10:13.740
to get a kid around town, a bicycle

00:10:13.740 --> 00:10:18.460
has got a lot of power.

00:10:18.460 --> 00:10:20.100
Key fans, we're here through Saturday.

00:10:20.100 --> 00:10:21.620
No, that's not applause, Fort.

00:10:21.620 --> 00:10:23.620
I'm looking for my keys.

00:10:23.620 --> 00:10:24.940
You mean you haven't found them yet?

00:10:24.940 --> 00:10:25.860
Oh, yeah, sure I have.

00:10:25.860 --> 00:10:28.500
Just long enough to put that key clapper gizmo on.

00:10:28.500 --> 00:10:29.340
How does it work, Dad?

00:10:29.340 --> 00:10:31.140
Well, I'm not exactly sure.

00:10:31.140 --> 00:10:34.500
I clap, it beeps, you follow the sound,

00:10:34.500 --> 00:10:36.460
it, you find your keys.

00:10:36.460 --> 00:10:39.100
Cool, so how long have you been looking for them?

00:10:39.100 --> 00:10:45.510
45 minutes.

00:10:45.510 --> 00:10:48.110
Seemed a lot more effective on the commercials.

00:10:48.110 --> 00:10:49.430
Dad, let me ask you something.

00:10:49.430 --> 00:10:50.950
Yeah, shoot.

00:10:50.990 --> 00:10:54.310
Well, what do you do if something of yours gets stolen?

00:10:54.310 --> 00:10:56.270
Oh, I don't think my keys were stolen.

00:10:56.270 --> 00:10:58.550
Me neither, Dad.

00:10:58.550 --> 00:11:01.960
It's my bike.

00:11:01.960 --> 00:11:03.680
You think your bike is stolen?

00:11:03.680 --> 00:11:06.200
I can't find it anywhere, Dad.

00:11:06.200 --> 00:11:07.520
Sport, I shouldn't have to tell you this.

00:11:07.520 --> 00:11:09.240
That's why the garage has a lock on it.

00:11:09.240 --> 00:11:10.600
I know.

00:11:10.600 --> 00:11:13.280
Stolen, in front of the house?

00:11:13.280 --> 00:11:15.320
Gone, so now what do I do?

00:11:15.320 --> 00:11:18.840
Well, let's see.

00:11:18.840 --> 00:11:20.560
You could just chalk it up to experience

00:11:20.560 --> 00:11:23.240
and accept that your bike is gone,

00:11:23.240 --> 00:11:25.080
or we could try and get it back.

00:11:25.080 --> 00:11:27.040
How'd we do that?

00:11:27.040 --> 00:11:28.280
Call the police?

00:11:28.280 --> 00:11:29.640
That sounds kind of drastic, Dad.

00:11:29.640 --> 00:11:30.920
Well, that's what they're there for.

00:11:30.920 --> 00:11:32.760
But aren't they busy busting bank robbers or something?

00:11:32.760 --> 00:11:34.960
Yeah, well, I'm sure they could squeeze you in.

00:11:34.960 --> 00:11:36.080
I'll go give them a call.

00:11:36.080 --> 00:11:38.920
Thanks, Dad, but you know, it's my bike.

00:11:38.920 --> 00:11:41.080
And I'm not a kid anymore.

00:11:41.080 --> 00:11:42.040
I'll call.

00:11:42.040 --> 00:11:50.120
OK, Sport, that's the way you want to study.

00:11:50.120 --> 00:11:51.480
The cops?

00:11:51.480 --> 00:11:53.240
Will they take me seriously?

00:11:53.240 --> 00:11:55.320
I mean, what if they laugh at me?

00:11:55.320 --> 00:11:57.200
Wait a minute, what right do they have to laugh at me?

00:11:57.200 --> 00:11:59.360
I mean, I pay taxes.

00:11:59.360 --> 00:12:03.080
Well, OK, not me exactly, but people I'm related to do.

00:12:03.080 --> 00:12:08.380
Only one way to find out.

00:12:08.380 --> 00:12:09.420
Hello, operator?

00:12:09.420 --> 00:12:11.380
Get me the police.

00:12:11.380 --> 00:12:17.100
I've always wanted to say that.

00:12:17.100 --> 00:12:18.180
That's the way you wear it, Mom.

00:12:18.180 --> 00:12:19.820
Well, I just want you to look nice for the police,

00:12:19.820 --> 00:12:33.650
as long as I'm not.

00:12:33.650 --> 00:12:35.010
Somebody call about a missing bike.

00:12:35.010 --> 00:12:35.930
That's me.

00:12:35.930 --> 00:12:37.210
Hi, I'm Janet Darling.

00:12:37.210 --> 00:12:39.330
Come on in.

00:12:39.330 --> 00:12:41.250
Mom, I think I can handle this by myself.

00:12:41.250 --> 00:12:42.290
OK, you go ahead.

00:12:42.290 --> 00:12:44.530
But I think I'll hang around a little.

00:12:44.530 --> 00:12:45.850
You close the darling?

00:12:45.850 --> 00:12:46.450
Uh-huh.

00:12:46.450 --> 00:12:47.890
I'm Officer Mustafa.

00:12:47.890 --> 00:12:49.250
This is Officer Baines.

00:12:49.250 --> 00:12:50.050
Hi.

00:12:50.050 --> 00:12:52.170
So you think you can catch whoever took my bike?

00:12:52.170 --> 00:12:53.290
Depends.

00:12:53.290 --> 00:12:54.730
You know who did it?

00:12:54.730 --> 00:12:55.570
Funny.

00:12:55.570 --> 00:12:57.130
Tell us about the bike.

00:12:57.130 --> 00:13:00.090
Well, I got it three years ago for my birthday.

00:13:00.090 --> 00:13:01.610
And it seemed like a big deal at the time,

00:13:01.610 --> 00:13:02.730
but what I really wanted is a car.

00:13:02.730 --> 00:13:04.330
But you know, you need to learn this permit first.

00:13:04.330 --> 00:13:04.770
We see.

00:13:04.770 --> 00:13:05.850
Back to the bike.

00:13:05.850 --> 00:13:07.250
Can you describe it?

00:13:07.250 --> 00:13:08.850
OK.

00:13:08.850 --> 00:13:10.650
It was a 26-inch girl's bike.

00:13:10.650 --> 00:13:12.650
And doesn't it have that cute license plate that says

00:13:12.650 --> 00:13:14.530
Clarissa on the back?

00:13:14.530 --> 00:13:18.090
Mom, I should've fed off two years ago.

00:13:18.090 --> 00:13:20.530
It was red with a wicker basket, three speed.

00:13:20.530 --> 00:13:21.850
Three speed.

00:13:21.850 --> 00:13:24.610
This is why I joined the force.

00:13:24.610 --> 00:13:25.890
When did you last see the bike?

00:13:25.890 --> 00:13:26.370
Monday.

00:13:26.370 --> 00:13:27.130
Uh-huh, where?

00:13:27.130 --> 00:13:27.930
In the front yard?

00:13:27.930 --> 00:13:28.650
Locked.

00:13:28.650 --> 00:13:29.730
Not exactly.

00:13:29.730 --> 00:13:31.130
Unlocked for a daylight?

00:13:31.130 --> 00:13:32.130
Unattended?

00:13:32.130 --> 00:13:32.930
Only for a minute.

00:13:32.930 --> 00:13:35.290
Can you imagine we were all in the house?

00:13:35.290 --> 00:13:36.130
Uh-huh.

00:13:36.130 --> 00:13:38.210
Are you getting all this down?

00:13:38.210 --> 00:13:40.130
Oh, yeah.

00:13:40.130 --> 00:13:43.010
We'll let you know if something turns up.

00:13:43.010 --> 00:13:43.810
Is that it?

00:13:43.810 --> 00:13:45.690
Well, what else did you expect them to do, dear?

00:13:45.690 --> 00:13:48.850
I suppose we could fingerprint the law.

00:13:48.850 --> 00:13:50.330
We'll do everything that we can.

00:13:50.330 --> 00:13:52.290
So you think you can get my bike back?

00:13:52.290 --> 00:13:53.090
It's hard to say.

00:13:53.090 --> 00:13:54.570
We see a lot of cases like this.

00:13:54.570 --> 00:13:56.330
Try not to get your hopes up.

00:13:56.330 --> 00:13:58.290
There isn't a very good recovery rate on bicycles.

00:13:58.290 --> 00:14:00.130
A bike gets stolen every three minutes.

00:14:00.130 --> 00:14:01.650
How often are they found?

00:14:01.650 --> 00:14:03.970
Let's just say we've been on this case for 10 minutes.

00:14:03.970 --> 00:14:05.610
We haven't recovered a bike yet.

00:14:05.610 --> 00:14:07.610
So you figure it out.

00:14:07.610 --> 00:14:08.450
It was nice meeting you.

00:14:08.450 --> 00:14:09.530
Well, so long.

00:14:09.530 --> 00:14:10.450
Thanks for coming.

00:14:10.450 --> 00:14:12.330
Yeah, thanks.

00:14:12.330 --> 00:14:13.650
I think.

00:14:13.650 --> 00:14:14.890
Boy, they weren't with Chelt.

00:14:14.890 --> 00:14:17.010
No, we don't know that yet, dear.

00:14:17.010 --> 00:14:17.510
I don't know.

00:14:17.510 --> 00:14:19.090
They just didn't seem to care.

00:14:19.090 --> 00:14:21.690
Cops on TV at least pretend to be interested.

00:14:21.690 --> 00:14:26.160
Let's wait and see what turns up.

00:14:26.160 --> 00:14:26.880
Great.

00:14:26.880 --> 00:14:28.240
By the time they find my bike,

00:14:28.240 --> 00:14:31.120
the only wheels I'll need will be on my wheelchair.

00:14:31.120 --> 00:14:32.440
If I really want my bike back,

00:14:32.440 --> 00:14:34.760
I'm going to have to go out and get it myself.

00:14:34.760 --> 00:14:36.680
Mom and dad won't responsible.

00:14:36.680 --> 00:14:38.360
I'll give them responsible.

00:14:38.360 --> 00:14:39.920
So what if I don't have any wheels?

00:14:39.960 --> 00:14:42.800
I can afford a little shoe leather finding my bike.

00:14:42.800 --> 00:14:44.960
Yeah, just like the old private eyes,

00:14:44.960 --> 00:14:46.480
I'll scour the neighborhood.

00:14:46.480 --> 00:14:48.800
I'll walk every inch of these mean straights.

00:14:48.800 --> 00:14:54.210
I can see it now.

00:14:54.210 --> 00:14:56.690
It was a cold, damp, and dingy night,

00:14:56.690 --> 00:14:58.850
like a sweat sock that had been worn to one gym class

00:14:58.850 --> 00:15:00.290
too many.

00:15:00.290 --> 00:15:01.530
But I didn't care.

00:15:01.530 --> 00:15:03.330
I had a job to do.

00:15:03.330 --> 00:15:05.450
It's easy losing a bike in this town,

00:15:05.450 --> 00:15:07.250
hard parts getting it back.

00:15:07.250 --> 00:15:08.770
That's where I come in.

00:15:08.770 --> 00:15:09.890
Name's Darling.

00:15:09.890 --> 00:15:11.850
Clarissa Darling, P.I.

00:15:11.850 --> 00:15:13.250
I got a tip from Willie the Mole

00:15:13.250 --> 00:15:16.130
that something fishy was going on down at the docks.

00:15:16.130 --> 00:15:19.250
And I don't mean hell of it.

00:15:19.250 --> 00:15:20.330
The docks.

00:15:20.330 --> 00:15:22.970
I hate the docks.

00:15:22.970 --> 00:15:27.130
Ordered a tuna salad, extra mayo.

00:15:27.130 --> 00:15:29.290
Translation, the bike I was looking for

00:15:29.290 --> 00:15:31.570
had a one-way ticket to Shanghai,

00:15:31.570 --> 00:15:34.250
unless somebody moved and fast.

00:15:34.250 --> 00:15:39.700
That somebody was me.

00:15:39.700 --> 00:15:45.580
Gentlemen, please, careful, careful.

00:15:45.580 --> 00:15:47.260
Happy to see me, Mr. Big.

00:15:47.260 --> 00:15:48.820
You're too late, my dear.

00:15:48.820 --> 00:15:53.260
Your precious bike is as good as gone.

00:15:53.260 --> 00:15:54.420
Oh, yeah?

00:15:54.420 --> 00:15:56.740
Tell that to my buddies in blue.

00:15:56.740 --> 00:15:57.820
Darling, we got your call.

00:15:57.820 --> 00:15:59.020
What's the big call?

00:15:59.020 --> 00:16:01.980
Mr. Big, we've got a nice place for you downtown.

00:16:01.980 --> 00:16:04.980
With bars on the window and everything.

00:16:04.980 --> 00:16:07.700
Game's set and matched to you, darling.

00:16:07.700 --> 00:16:10.980
But next time, I serve.

00:16:10.980 --> 00:16:12.540
You can start serving now.

00:16:12.540 --> 00:16:14.980
Five to 15 for bike theft.

00:16:14.980 --> 00:16:24.700
All this fishing, he's starting to stink.

00:16:24.700 --> 00:16:27.060
Well, I still don't have a clue as to where my bike is,

00:16:27.060 --> 00:16:29.860
but it looks like the big wheel will spin tonight.

00:16:29.860 --> 00:16:32.300
Translation, I got to get my bike back.

00:16:32.300 --> 00:16:34.100
And the only way to do that is to get out there

00:16:34.100 --> 00:16:40.200
and kick up some dirt.

00:16:40.200 --> 00:16:43.120
Nuff, nuff, nuff, nuff, nuff, nuff, nuff, nuff, nuff,

00:16:43.120 --> 00:16:44.120
do it.

00:16:44.120 --> 00:16:48.920
More Clarissa, more Snake after this.

00:16:48.920 --> 00:16:50.120
How many combinations?

00:16:50.120 --> 00:16:50.840
Combinations?

00:16:50.840 --> 00:16:51.640
In every bag.

00:16:51.640 --> 00:16:52.120
Skittles.

00:16:52.120 --> 00:16:53.400
Of Skittles, bites, ice candy.

00:16:53.400 --> 00:16:55.120
Let's do this one bag at a time.

00:16:55.160 --> 00:16:56.200
Well, there's Stropa Berry.

00:16:56.200 --> 00:16:57.080
We got Lemla Mora.

00:16:57.080 --> 00:16:57.800
Or a Grapele.

00:16:57.800 --> 00:16:58.520
And Berry Lime.

00:16:58.520 --> 00:16:59.080
Berry Lime.

00:16:59.080 --> 00:17:00.040
Look, this is how it works.

00:17:00.040 --> 00:17:00.520
OK.

00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:01.800
Then there's Stropa Santa.

00:17:01.800 --> 00:17:02.480
Banna Melbour.

00:17:02.480 --> 00:17:03.080
Stropa Nanna.

00:17:03.080 --> 00:17:03.840
Casaberry.

00:17:03.840 --> 00:17:04.360
Good.

00:17:04.360 --> 00:17:05.720
See, every Skittles combination

00:17:05.720 --> 00:17:06.480
is a new taste.

00:17:06.480 --> 00:17:07.120
With a new name.

00:17:07.120 --> 00:17:07.840
Well, for example.

00:17:07.840 --> 00:17:09.240
Grapele Sour Apple Cherries.

00:17:09.240 --> 00:17:09.960
Lemon Melbour Lime.

00:17:09.960 --> 00:17:11.240
Lemon Melbour Lime.

00:17:11.240 --> 00:17:12.280
Lemon Melbour Lime.

00:17:12.280 --> 00:17:13.680
So how many combinations are there?

00:17:13.680 --> 00:17:14.480
Hello.

00:17:14.480 --> 00:17:15.400
Find out for yourself.

00:17:15.400 --> 00:17:16.920
Taste the rainbow.

00:17:16.920 --> 00:17:17.720
Don't forget the world.

00:17:17.720 --> 00:17:18.400
Churber Fuber.

00:17:18.400 --> 00:17:20.280
OK.

00:17:20.280 --> 00:17:21.560
Morphin Time.

00:17:21.560 --> 00:17:23.320
Muddy Morphin Underwear.

00:17:23.320 --> 00:17:24.080
Let's do it.

00:17:24.080 --> 00:17:25.520
Fire.

00:17:25.520 --> 00:17:28.920
You can pretend to have Megazord power.

00:17:28.920 --> 00:17:30.760
In your mighty Morphin Power Rangers

00:17:30.760 --> 00:17:33.200
underwear, by fruit of the loom.

00:17:33.200 --> 00:17:36.300
Power up.

00:17:36.300 --> 00:17:37.500
Mom.

00:17:37.500 --> 00:17:39.420
Play School Dollhouse.

00:17:39.420 --> 00:17:41.100
And now you can get even more great stuff

00:17:41.100 --> 00:17:43.100
for your Play School Dollhouse.

00:17:43.100 --> 00:17:45.180
My big sister has a new convertible.

00:17:45.180 --> 00:17:47.260
And she loves driving sour around.

00:17:47.260 --> 00:17:48.820
We've got a washer and dryer.

00:17:48.820 --> 00:17:50.540
Then I can use them myself.

00:17:50.540 --> 00:17:51.980
Mom redecorated our room.

00:17:51.980 --> 00:17:53.380
And we got funk bits.

00:17:53.380 --> 00:17:56.340
And we even got a barbecue set for the backyard.

00:17:56.340 --> 00:17:57.580
I love this house.

00:17:57.580 --> 00:18:00.060
It's my Play School Dollhouse.

00:18:00.060 --> 00:18:02.700
Play School Dollhouse and accessory set sold separately.

00:18:02.700 --> 00:18:06.300
Batteries not included.

00:18:06.300 --> 00:18:07.100
Watching.

00:18:07.100 --> 00:18:07.980
Nick.

00:18:07.980 --> 00:18:26.800
And now back to Clarissa Explains It All.

00:18:26.800 --> 00:18:28.640
I wanted to have my stolen bike back in time

00:18:28.640 --> 00:18:30.120
to go to the movies tonight.

00:18:30.120 --> 00:18:32.320
I was all charged up to look for it.

00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:34.400
But after spending a couple days running around,

00:18:34.400 --> 00:18:36.200
I think my battery's worn out.

00:18:36.200 --> 00:18:37.920
Here are some of the things I did.

00:18:37.920 --> 00:18:40.920
First, I put posters up all over town.

00:18:40.920 --> 00:18:42.280
Didn't get any response.

00:18:42.280 --> 00:18:43.040
It's true.

00:18:43.040 --> 00:18:44.960
Reading is a dying art.

00:18:44.960 --> 00:18:46.760
Then I went door to door asking if anybody'd

00:18:46.760 --> 00:18:48.920
seen any suspicious characters.

00:18:48.920 --> 00:18:51.200
Nobody had anything to say about my bike.

00:18:51.200 --> 00:18:52.840
But the whole neighborhood is talking about Mr.

00:18:52.840 --> 00:18:54.360
Babelbrook's new to pay.

00:18:54.360 --> 00:18:56.880
Turns out he isn't fooling anyone.

00:18:56.880 --> 00:18:58.000
I went to the used bike store

00:18:58.000 --> 00:18:59.480
to see if somebody sold it.

00:18:59.480 --> 00:19:00.640
Saw a lot of bikes.

00:19:00.640 --> 00:19:01.720
None of them were mine.

00:19:01.720 --> 00:19:03.920
The worst part is I had to walk everywhere.

00:19:03.920 --> 00:19:06.880
If only I had a bike, finding my bike would be easier.

00:19:06.920 --> 00:19:09.360
Should I really have to deal with this at my age?

00:19:09.360 --> 00:19:10.720
Am I reduced to begging for rides

00:19:10.720 --> 00:19:15.190
until I get my license?

00:19:15.190 --> 00:19:16.430
Kind of, Clarissa. Why?

00:19:16.430 --> 00:19:17.950
Well, what about later? Are you busy later?

00:19:17.950 --> 00:19:18.870
What's on your mind?

00:19:18.870 --> 00:19:20.670
I'm looking for a ride to the multiplex.

00:19:20.670 --> 00:19:22.230
Sorry, dear. I've already run my errands.

00:19:22.230 --> 00:19:23.550
Plus, I have to finish this budget

00:19:23.550 --> 00:19:24.990
for the children's museum.

00:19:24.990 --> 00:19:26.350
I'm never going to get anywhere.

00:19:26.350 --> 00:19:28.070
Well, there is another solution, you know.

00:19:28.070 --> 00:19:29.310
You'll let me drive?

00:19:29.310 --> 00:19:32.510
No. I mean you can borrow your brother's bike.

00:19:32.510 --> 00:19:33.550
I'd rather walk.

00:19:33.550 --> 00:19:36.840
Well, it's up to you.

00:19:36.840 --> 00:19:37.720
Great.

00:19:37.720 --> 00:19:39.960
The perfect ending to a lousy day.

00:19:39.960 --> 00:19:41.680
Crumbling to Ferg-Wad for help.

00:19:41.680 --> 00:19:50.130
Well, I guess you got to crawl before you can ride.

00:19:50.130 --> 00:19:51.330
The cunning move.

00:19:51.330 --> 00:19:52.690
Knock, knock, knock.

00:19:52.690 --> 00:19:55.210
Who is it?

00:19:55.210 --> 00:19:57.210
Can I talk to you a minute, Ferguson?

00:19:57.210 --> 00:19:58.890
Ferguson?

00:19:58.890 --> 00:20:03.210
Ferguson, not Ferg-Wad, Ferg-Turt, or Ferg-Grat?

00:20:03.210 --> 00:20:04.850
Somebody must want something.

00:20:04.850 --> 00:20:09.480
Enter.

00:20:09.480 --> 00:20:10.480
I need a favor.

00:20:10.480 --> 00:20:12.840
Well, I'm a reasonable man.

00:20:12.840 --> 00:20:13.960
Ask away.

00:20:13.960 --> 00:20:15.880
I need your bike just for tonight.

00:20:15.880 --> 00:20:16.960
My bike?

00:20:16.960 --> 00:20:18.360
You want to borrow my bike?

00:20:18.360 --> 00:20:19.440
Do you have to rub it in?

00:20:19.440 --> 00:20:20.240
Have to?

00:20:20.240 --> 00:20:22.520
Nah, I choose to.

00:20:22.520 --> 00:20:24.720
Besides, this is from the woman who begrudged me

00:20:24.720 --> 00:20:27.560
not only a computer, but a ruler as well.

00:20:27.560 --> 00:20:30.520
This I'm asking first, and believe me, it's painful.

00:20:30.520 --> 00:20:33.120
Oh, let's dwell on that a moment.

00:20:33.120 --> 00:20:34.640
OK, you can use my computer.

00:20:34.640 --> 00:20:37.000
Nope, too little, too late, too bad.

00:20:37.000 --> 00:20:38.880
Besides, I handed that before days ago.

00:20:38.880 --> 00:20:40.920
Come on, Ferguson, just lend it to me.

00:20:40.920 --> 00:20:44.080
No, sis, because while I understand your needs,

00:20:44.080 --> 00:20:45.600
somebody's got to look out for mine.

00:20:45.600 --> 00:20:46.680
What are you talking about?

00:20:46.680 --> 00:20:51.640
Well, suppose, just suppose I lent you my bike.

00:20:51.640 --> 00:20:53.120
Would that be prudent?

00:20:53.120 --> 00:20:56.560
We have clear evidence that a bike is not safe in your hands.

00:20:56.560 --> 00:20:57.880
I'll lock it up.

00:20:57.880 --> 00:21:00.480
Oh, and then there's the wear and tear in the tires.

00:21:00.480 --> 00:21:05.450
I'll give you a dollar.

00:21:05.450 --> 00:21:06.450
You're on.

00:21:06.450 --> 00:21:11.590
Come with me.

00:21:11.590 --> 00:21:13.070
Wait, you must be joking.

00:21:13.070 --> 00:21:16.430
This is your crummy old bike that clipped a raptor on a tree.

00:21:16.430 --> 00:21:18.190
You never specified making model.

00:21:18.190 --> 00:21:19.110
Happy riding.

00:21:19.110 --> 00:21:19.510
Forget it.

00:21:19.510 --> 00:21:21.950
Give me the rock band of $4,000 or my dollar back.

00:21:21.990 --> 00:21:23.510
Sorry, sis, I can't make that deal.

00:21:23.510 --> 00:21:26.350
But I'll tell you what, you take this one off my hands

00:21:26.350 --> 00:21:27.790
for $10 even.

00:21:27.790 --> 00:21:29.870
With a little work, it can be a real beaut.

00:21:29.870 --> 00:21:31.230
I can't believe this.

00:21:31.230 --> 00:21:32.430
Take it or leave it.

00:21:32.430 --> 00:21:36.470
Let me see if I've got it.

00:21:36.470 --> 00:21:41.110
Here's a one, a five, and four more ones.

00:21:41.110 --> 00:21:42.390
Thank you.

00:21:42.390 --> 00:21:43.270
Thank you.

00:21:43.270 --> 00:21:46.630
I think I'll add this to my presidential portrait collection.

00:21:46.630 --> 00:21:48.430
Goodbye, my dear old bike.

00:21:48.430 --> 00:21:50.270
Take good care of it, sis.

00:21:50.270 --> 00:21:52.270
I've got a lot of fond memories of my riding

00:21:52.270 --> 00:21:53.870
days with this bike.

00:21:53.910 --> 00:21:56.390
If these folks could talk, they'd say.

00:21:56.390 --> 00:21:58.270
Shut up.

00:21:58.270 --> 00:22:01.780
OK.

00:22:01.780 --> 00:22:03.260
Great.

00:22:03.260 --> 00:22:06.660
Here I am ready for a four-in-the-floor convertible.

00:22:06.660 --> 00:22:09.980
And I'm forced to ride my little brother's two-wheel leftovers.

00:22:09.980 --> 00:22:11.140
Well, I made that ground a bike,

00:22:11.140 --> 00:22:13.020
but it looks like I still need a bike.

00:22:13.020 --> 00:22:19.980
I'm either stuck with this thing or I'm stuck at home.

00:22:19.980 --> 00:22:25.180
OK, you put on new brake pads, new wheels, new fork,

00:22:25.180 --> 00:22:28.420
straighten out the handlebars, and attach to new fender.

00:22:28.420 --> 00:22:29.740
So when you think about it,

00:22:29.780 --> 00:22:30.580
for 10 bucks?

00:22:30.580 --> 00:22:33.300
10 bucks after what I spent on parts?

00:22:33.300 --> 00:22:34.380
You saved on labor.

00:22:34.380 --> 00:22:35.580
Yeah, thanks, Sam.

00:22:35.580 --> 00:22:37.300
You're real whiz with the wrench.

00:22:37.300 --> 00:22:39.100
Hey, we worked together.

00:22:39.100 --> 00:22:43.660
And I've got to say, we really got it to look like a bike.

00:22:43.660 --> 00:22:45.540
Who would have believed?

00:22:45.540 --> 00:22:49.080
Yeah, we really did do a good job.

00:22:49.080 --> 00:22:50.760
Hi, Dad. What have you got there?

00:22:50.760 --> 00:22:53.680
Ah, the end of my key dilemma, the key rack.

00:22:53.680 --> 00:22:54.760
Did you make that yourself?

00:22:54.760 --> 00:22:55.880
Sure did.

00:22:55.880 --> 00:22:57.120
Where are you going to put it, Dad?

00:22:57.120 --> 00:22:58.800
Oh, right inside the kitchen door.

00:22:58.800 --> 00:23:00.080
There's a hook for each one of us.

00:23:00.080 --> 00:23:02.120
This way we'll have all of our keys, all in a row,

00:23:02.120 --> 00:23:05.160
all together, right by the door.

00:23:05.160 --> 00:23:07.560
So anyone who breaks in will have total access

00:23:07.560 --> 00:23:08.800
to everything we own.

00:23:08.800 --> 00:23:09.680
Nice try, Dad.

00:23:09.680 --> 00:23:10.840
Yeah, all right.

00:23:10.840 --> 00:23:14.360
Well, maybe I can use it for a belt rack.

00:23:14.360 --> 00:23:16.360
Your family sure has trouble hanging on to things.

00:23:16.360 --> 00:23:17.440
And then there are those things

00:23:17.440 --> 00:23:20.320
we can't get rid of no matter how hard we try.

00:23:20.320 --> 00:23:21.760
You fixed it up?

00:23:21.760 --> 00:23:22.920
Well, yeah, you fixed it up.

00:23:22.920 --> 00:23:24.960
I mean, how much did you spend?

